A3: SPL Library Checkouts

Introduction

The data that I will be analyzing is from the Seattle Public Library. My main focus will be on analyzing the data of the types of books people have checked out during the years of 2020-2022

Summary Information

I want to try and answer these following questions:

How did COVID affect the physical and digital checkout with books in 2020? - I will be first grouping the physical and digital types of books within a category, then I will calculate the total checkouts between the both within the year of 2020 by months, then I will plot the data with two line plots

Who was the most popular author between 2020-2022? - I first grouped all the authors by the total amount of checkouts they have. Then I proceeded to sort the data to see who was in the top between 2020-2022. Then I only grabbed top 10 and plot the data with a column graph.

What top 5 types of books was the most popular during 2020-2022? - I first filtered the data to only material types, then I sorted the data from the highest to lowest checkouts. To find the top 5 I grabbed only the first 5 within the sorted data then I plotted it in a piechart!

Calculated values: 1. Physical checkouts in 2020’s months 2. Digital checkouts in 2020’s months 3. All the author’s checkouts in total 4. Top ten authors within 2020-2022 5. Top five most checked out material type books within 2020-2022

Digital vs Physical checkouts during 2020.

Include a chart. Make sure to describe why you included the chart, and what patterns emerged

These two charts is being presented to explore the changes between the digital and physical checkouts especially during the rise of COVID during 2020.

As we can see that the hardcover checkouts dropped and digital checkouts was on a rise. This pattern made sense for book checkouts because during the pandemic the lockdown was strongly affecting the types of checkouts people were doing.
